    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1115" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀοιδός</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οῦ</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀείδω</span>):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">singer, bard;</span> enumerated among the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δημιοεργοί</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            17.383</span></i> ff; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐτοδίδακτος</span>
          (implying inspiration), <i><span class="en">Od. 22.347</span></i>;
          in Il. only <i><span class="en">Il. 24.720</span></i>. For the high
          estimation in which the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀοιδός</span> was
          held, see <i><span class="en">Od. 8.479</span></i> ff.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
